The runtime error was triggered because `map-edit-view.js` expected the first
argument passed by Saltcorn to be a **Field object**, while Saltcorn actually
passes just the **field name string**.  
This broke every “edit” view that relies on the Leaflet map editor.

While addressing the crash I aligned the plug‑in with the three edit‑view
variants you described:

1. `edit` – fully‑interactive Leaflet map (create / edit / delete).  
2. `raw` – plain‑text editor + optional map preview button.  
3. `map` – read‑only map preview (useful when the form should be immutable).

The non‑edit “show” view remains unchanged for display contexts.

The fix touches only two files but fully resolves the issue across all
PostGIS‑backed field types.

